# PakFactory stack (Cursor)

Read [`AGENTS.md`](../../AGENTS.md) at the repository root for full stack, domain, MCP, ADR summary, and JIRA defaults. Blog 3.0 shipped rules (PROD-1480 epic): [`docs/blog-3-jira-conventions.md`](../../docs/blog-3-jira-conventions.md).

**Non‑negotiable highlights:**

- **Package manager:** **pnpm 9.x** only — never `npm install` or `yarn` at the repo root for this project.
- **Stack:** Turborepo monorepo; Next.js 16 (App Router); React 19; Tailwind 4; Sanity 5; Node ≥ 20.19.
- **Domain:** This is **not** a Shopify storefront. No carts, checkout, or generic e‑commerce PDP flows unless explicitly requested. Prefer quote / RFQ / consultative CTAs.
- **UI primitives:** Do not edit `packages/ui/src/components` or shared `globals.css` for new features; do not change global shell (`layout.tsx`, navbar) unless the task asks. See [`workspace-instructions.mdc`](workspace-instructions.mdc).
- **Studio SEO/Social fields:** every blog content type declares SEO + Social fields through the shared helper [`apps/studio/lib/seo-fields.ts`](../../apps/studio/lib/seo-fields.ts) (`seoFields(...)` + `socialFields(...)`) — do **not** hand-redeclare `metaTitle`/`metaDescription`/`ogImage` per schema. Robots toggles are **`allowIndex` / `allowFollow` / `noImageIndex`** (not inverted `noindex`); `canonical` only where `canonical: true` is passed (post, blogPage). Field defaults live in the helper; **fallbacks resolve in the GROQ/front-end layer**, not the schema. Page-builder schemas live in `apps/studio/schemas/blocks/` (terminology is "block", per ADR-012; content `_type`s unchanged).
- **Sanity content:** agents edit **schemas in git only** — never write documents (no seeds, no MCP create/patch/publish) on any dataset. Humans run seeds and Studio edits. See [`AGENTS.md`](../../AGENTS.md) § Sanity content — agent guardrails.

For blog-specific routes, queries, and schema rules, when editing `apps/blog/**` Cursor also applies [`apps/blog/.cursor/rules/blog.mdc`](../../apps/blog/.cursor/rules/blog.mdc).
